<div id="outline-container-org2f5d567" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org2f5d567">Linear Data Structures</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2f5d567">
<p>
A Linear data struct is one that is arranged sequentially in memory
They also have only one predeccesor and one successor
Examples:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Stack</li>
<li>Array</li>
<li>Queue</li>
<li>Linked list</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org62111ff" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org62111ff">None Linear Data Structures</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org62111ff">
<p>
A non linear data struct is one that is not arrange in a sequential order.
Examples:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Tree</li>
<li>Graph</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgff7aa9f" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgff7aa9f">Static Data Structs</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgff7aa9f">
<p>
memory is allocated at compile time
Max size is always fixed
</p>

<p>
Examples:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Array</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org12da244" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org12da244">Dynamic data structs</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org12da244">
<p>
memory is allocated at run time, it is flexible
</p>

<p>
Example:
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Linked list</li>
</ul>
